  "day": 8,
  "key": "day_8_care_and_boundary",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-01",
  "title": {
    "en": "God’s Loving Care and Protective Boundaries"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "Even after disobedience, God shows care for the man and the woman.",
      "At the same time, He sets boundaries to protect life and uphold His purpose."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "care",
        "icon": "checkroom",
        "label": { "en": "God Covers Their Shame" },
        "lines": [
          "The Lord God made garments of skin",
          "for Adam and his wife",
          "and clothed them."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "knowledge",
        "icon": "psychology",
        "label": { "en": "Knowledge and Limitation" },
        "lines": [
          "The Lord God said,",
          "“The man has now become like one of us,",
          "knowing good and evil.",
          "He must not be allowed",
          "to reach out his hand",
          "and take also from the tree of life",
          "and eat,",
          "and live forever.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "removal",
        "icon": "exit_to_app",
        "label": { "en": "Removed from the Garden" },
        "lines": [
          "So the Lord God banished him",
          "from the Garden of Eden",
          "to work the ground",
          "from which he had been taken."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "guarding",
        "icon": "security",
        "label": { "en": "The Way Is Guarded" },
        "lines": [
          "After He drove the man out,",
          "He placed on the east side",
          "of the Garden of Eden",
          "cherubim",
          "and a flaming sword",
          "flashing back and forth",
          "to guard the way",
          "to the tree of life."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What do you notice about how God shows care while also setting firm boundaries in this passage?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Genesis 3:21–24"]
  }
}
